===============================================================================

Validrb has been installed!

Created:
  - config/initializers/validrb.rb  (configuration)
  - app/forms/application_form.rb   (base form class)
  - app/forms/                      (form objects directory)
  - app/schemas/                    (schema definitions directory)

Quick Start:

1. Create a form object:

   # app/forms/user_form.rb
   class UserForm < ApplicationForm
     schema do
       field :name, :string, min: 2
       field :email, :string, format: :email
       field :password, :string, min: 8
     end
   end

2. Use in controller:

   class UsersController < ApplicationController
     def create
       @form = UserForm.new(user_params)
       if @form.valid?
         @user = User.create!(@form.attributes)
         redirect_to @user
       else
         render :new, status: :unprocessable_entity
       end
     end

     private

     def user_params
       params.require(:user).permit(:name, :email, :password)
     end
   end

3. Use in views:

   <%= form_with model: @form, url: users_path do |f| %>
     <%= f.text_field :name %>
     <%= f.email_field :email %>
     <%= f.password_field :password %>
     <%= f.submit %>
   <% end %>

Generate more forms:

   rails g validrb:form RegistrationForm name:string email:string:email

Documentation: https://github.com/your-repo/validrb

===============================================================================
